      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cell Phones and Health</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>N M Swerdlow letter comments on research on cancer risks associated with cell phones (July 27 articel)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It is interesting to learn that 400 million cell phones will be sold this year. It is very interesting to learn that the Federal Communications Commission limit on close bodily exposure to radio waves is 1.6 watts per kilogram of human flesh. It is even more interesting to learn that genetically predisposed mice in Australia developed twice as many brain cancers when exposed to cell phone radiation. But the article did not answer the most interesting question of all: How many Australian mice will purchase cell phones this year?</p>
        <p>N.M. SWERDLOW  Chicago</p>
      </block>
